description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 4 Senior Administrator/Personal Assistant to work alongside and support the Specialist Services manager and CAMHS Transformation Lead within HCT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: Part time 22.5hrs per week (0.6wte)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contract Type: 6 months Secondment/Fixed Term Contract (FTC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Base: Trust HQ in Howard Court, Welwyn Garden City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working without supervision, you will provide administrative service and support to the Service Manager and CAMHS Transformation Lead. The role requires self-management of delegated and adhoc tasks and the knowledge and experience to determine the best solution to issues that may occur.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Along with the duties mentioned within the job description, your day to day accountabilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management and co-ordination of Manager/Leads diary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and management of the Manager’s email Inboxes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being a key point of contact for relevant enquiries from clinicians, internal and external stakeholders at senior levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaison with colleagues across the CAMHS system on behalf of the manager/lead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automation and Distribution of Information and reports internally and across the CAMHS system partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparation of information and papers for meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management of Action Trackers/Note taking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting and Updating of staff systems/records e.g. ESR /Personal folders/TRAC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management of relevant finance processes within scope of role e.g. raising purchase orders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to maintain a high degree of professionalism when working in settings where there is a fast pace of change, and be flexible in your approach having resilience under pressure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the basic salary, this post attracts a High Cost Area Supplement of 5% of basic salary subject to a minimum and a maximum payment per annum, pro rata where applicable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full valid driving license and access to a car to use regularly for business purposes is essential (unless you have a disability as defined by the Equality Act 2010).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will take place via video conferencing on Monday 16th Nov 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Mary Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Specialist Services Manager/CAMHS Transformation Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: mary.smith41@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07824889396&lt;/p&gt;
